A 25-year-old man was left seriously injured on Monday morning following an armed robbery outside a bank on Old Main Road in Hillcrest, KwaZulu-Natal. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said when paramedics arrived at the scene around 11.30 am,Â  the man was lying outside the entrance of the bank. He said the man had a gunshot wound to his leg, leaving him in a serious condition. He was taken to hospital for treatment. Meiring said local authorities and security services were already at the scene.